If you want to utilize remember-clt for your own Google account, you have to download a "client-secret.json". This is necessary to use the Google Calendar API.

For instructions on how to do this, see below:

1) Use this wizard (https://console.developers.google.com/flows/enableapi?apiid=calendar) to create or select a project in the Google Developers Console and automatically enable the API. Click the Go to credentials button to continue.

2) At the top of the page, select the OAuth consent screen tab. Select an Email address, enter a Product name if not already set, and click the Save button

3) Back on the Credentials tab, click the Add credentials button and select OAuth 2.0 client ID.

4) Select the application type Other and click the Create button.

5) Click OK to dismiss the resulting dialog.

6) Click the  (Download JSON) button to the right of the client ID. Move this file to your working directory and rename it client_secret.json.
